    "body": "I also noticed that and traced through the code realizing that the presets are always overwritten by networks and none of the networks uses the minimal configuration, so even the default node options use a mainnet preset, therefore overriding any attempt to use a minimal preset.\r\n\r\nThat said, it might be worth refactoring the entire preset/network logic because there is literally no reason to use a network without a preset. we can keep the presets as templates but no longer expose them to the users and rather just reference them internally for the various networks.\r\n\r\neasiest path of action would be to create a `dev` network that uses `minimal` to avoid falling back to default values. that said, I'm not entirely sure how involved this would be and would be happy to get a 2nd opinion on that.",
